    "The intrinsic flaw of this criteria is that the detection is rewarded generously while pulsing false alarm is penalized just once [30].",
    "Garg et al. [33] revise the primitive PA from an event perspective.",
    "Each anomaly segment is treated as an individual event and contributes to a true positive or false negative only once.",
    "This criterion, namely event-wise PA, prevents the inflated evaluation scores originated from illogical criteria, while absolutely overlooking the length of the anomaly segments.",
    "Based on the observation c, we apply a severity coefficient ln (k + e) to adjust the true positive and false positive measurements associated with the given anomalous segment of length k. The criterion is called reduced-length PA, and we categorize it along with event-wise PA as event-based evaluation criteria."
